# UI Components and Styling Standards

## Component Structure
- Components should be organized by FSD (Feature-Sliced Design) architecture
- Use shadcn/ui as the base component library
- Implement responsive design using Tailwind breakpoints

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS classes in the following order:
  1. Layout (position, display)
  2. Spacing (margin, padding)
  3. Sizing (width, height)
  4. Typography
  5. Visual (colors, backgrounds)

## Color Palette: Midnight Slate
- Primary: sky-500 (#0ea5e9)
- Secondary: slate-800 (#1e293b)
- Success: green-500 (#22c55e)
- Warning: amber-600 (#d97706)
- Background: slate-50 (#f8fafc)
- Text: slate-600 (#475569)

## Component Best Practices
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Add loading states for async operations
- Include error boundaries
- Use proper TypeScript types

## Chart Components
- Use Chart.js for circular/doughnut charts
- Use recharts for analytics visualizations
- Implement responsive chart containers
- Add proper tooltips and legends

## Layout Components
- Use container classes for consistent width
- Implement proper spacing with gap utilities
- Use grid system for responsive layouts
- Add proper padding for mobile/desktop
